title: From the Thames to the Trosachs.
author: Thompson, E. H.
snippet: The abbey contains the royal tombs of the Plantagenets, the House of Lancaster, the Tudors, the Stuarts, the Commonwealth,  and the House of Hanover ; and here are placed memorial  tablets of eminent English statesmen, philanthropists, poets, divines, men of letters and science, actors, artists, and musicians, some of whom are buried here, and some are not.
